can we send email notification , artificats using post action?

Yes â€” you can send email notifications and archive artifacts using the post action, but the method depends on whether you're using:

Freestyle Job

Pipeline (Jenkinsfile)

Letâ€™s break it down clearly.

âœ… 1. In Freestyle Jobs â†’ Post-Build Actions (UI)

Here, you do NOT use a Jenkinsfile.
Instead, you use the Jenkins UI.

âœ” You can send email from Post-Build actions

Go to:

Job â†’ Configure â†’ Post-build Actions â†’ Add â†’ Email Notification

âœ” You can archive artifacts from Post-Build actions
Job â†’ Configure â†’ Post-build Actions â†’ Add â†’ Archive the artifacts


So yes, in freestyle jobs, both email & artifacts are available through Post-Build Actions.

âœ… 2. In Pipeline (Jenkinsfile) â†’ post { } section

In Pipelines, email and artifact handling are done inside the post section.

ğŸ“Œ YES, you can do both inside post
Let's show how.

ğŸ“§ Sending Email Notification in Post Section
âœ” Using the mail step (Mail plugin required):
pipeline {
    agent any

    stages {
        stage('Build') {
            steps {
                echo "Building the project..."
            }
        }
    }

    post {
        success {
            mail to: 'team@example.com',
                 subject: "Build SUCCESS: ${env.JOB_NAME}",
                 body: "Build completed successfully!"
        }
        failure {
            mail to: 'team@example.com',
                 subject: "Build FAILED: ${env.JOB_NAME}",
                 body: "Please check the Jenkins logs."
        }
    }
}

ğŸ“¦ Archiving Artifacts in the Post Section

Use the archiveArtifacts step.

âœ” Example:
post {
    success {
        archiveArtifacts artifacts: 'build/*.jar', fingerprint: true
    }
}


This will archive all JAR files from the build/ directory only if build succeeds.

ğŸ§¹ You can also clean workspace in post
post {
    always {
        cleanWs()
    }
}

ğŸ”¥ Combined Example â†’ Email + Artifacts + Cleanup
pipeline {
    agent any
    
    stages {
        stage('Build') {
            steps {
                echo "Building the application..."
                sh 'mkdir -p build && echo "Sample file" > build/output.txt'
            }
        }
    }
    
    post {
        success {
            echo "Build was successful!"
            archiveArtifacts artifacts: 'build/*', fingerprint: true
            mail to: 'team@example.com',
                 subject: "Build SUCCESS: ${env.JOB_NAME}",
                 body: "Build completed. Artifacts archived."
        }
        failure {
            mail to: 'team@example.com',
                 subject: "Build FAILED: ${env.JOB_NAME}",
                 body: "Pipeline failed. Check Jenkins console logs."
        }
        always {
            cleanWs()
        }
    }
}

ğŸŸ¢ Final Answer
âœ” YES â€” You can send email notifications using post actions
âœ” YES â€” You can archive artifacts using post actions

But:

Job Type	How Itâ€™s Done
Freestyle Job	UI â†’ Post-Build Actions
Pipeline Job (Jenkinsfile)	Inside post { } section

