i have doubt like where we will store backup of the jenkins for each method and after that how we will restore it ?

Got it! Letâ€™s clarify exactly where backups are stored for each method and how restoration works in Jenkins. Iâ€™ll break it method by method.

1ï¸âƒ£ Manual Backup
Where the backup is stored

You decide the folder when you copy $JENKINS_HOME.

Example:

sudo cp -r /var/lib/jenkins /backup/jenkins_backup


Here:

Source â†’ /var/lib/jenkins (Jenkins home)

Backup â†’ /backup/jenkins_backup (your storage location)

Can also use an external drive, NAS, or cloud folder (like /mnt/nfs/jenkins_backup or /backup/s3/jenkins_backup).

How to restore

Stop Jenkins:

sudo systemctl stop jenkins


Replace $JENKINS_HOME with backup:

sudo rm -rf /var/lib/jenkins
sudo cp -r /backup/jenkins_backup /var/lib/jenkins


Fix permissions:

sudo chown -R jenkins:jenkins /var/lib/jenkins


Start Jenkins:

sudo systemctl start jenkins

2ï¸âƒ£ ThinBackup Plugin
Where the backup is stored

Configurable in ThinBackup settings:

Example: /backup/jenkins_thinbackup

ThinBackup creates zipped archives for each backup.

You can also schedule backups to remote storage (NFS, cloud).

How to restore

Go to Jenkins â†’ Manage Jenkins â†’ ThinBackup â†’ Restore

Select the backup to restore.

Plugin automatically restores:

Jobs

Configs

Plugins

Users & credentials

âš  Workspace and build logs can be optionally restored.

3ï¸âƒ£ Shell Script + Cron Backup
Where the backup is stored

Your script defines the directory.

BACKUP_DIR="/backup/jenkins"
DATE=$(date +%F)
tar -czf $BACKUP_DIR/jenkins-$DATE.tar.gz /var/lib/jenkins


/backup/jenkins is the storage location.

Each backup has a timestamped archive (jenkins-2025-12-13.tar.gz).

You can also store:

Local disk

NFS mount

S3 bucket using aws s3 cp after creating tar.gz

How to restore

Stop Jenkins:

sudo systemctl stop jenkins


Extract backup:

sudo tar -xzf /backup/jenkins/jenkins-2025-12-13.tar.gz -C /var/lib/jenkins


Fix permissions:

sudo chown -R jenkins:jenkins /var/lib/jenkins


Start Jenkins:

sudo systemctl start jenkins

4ï¸âƒ£ Docker Jenkins Backup
Where the backup is stored

If Jenkins is running in Docker, $JENKINS_HOME is usually a container volume: /var/jenkins_home

Backup command example:

docker cp jenkins:/var/jenkins_home ./jenkins_backup


This saves backup to host folder ./jenkins_backup

Can also copy to remote storage or cloud

How to restore

Stop Jenkins container:

docker stop jenkins


Copy backup into container volume:

docker cp ./jenkins_backup/. jenkins:/var/jenkins_home


Fix permissions inside container (if needed):

docker exec jenkins chown -R jenkins:jenkins /var/jenkins_home


Start container:

docker start jenkins

ğŸ“ Summary Table
Backup Method	Storage Location	Restore Method
Manual copy	Any folder you choose (/backup/jenkins_backup)	Stop Jenkins â†’ copy back â†’ fix permissions â†’ start Jenkins
ThinBackup plugin	Configurable in Jenkins (zipped backups)	Use ThinBackup â†’ Restore UI
Shell script + Cron	Defined in script (/backup/jenkins/jenkins-<date>.tar.gz)	Stop Jenkins â†’ extract tar.gz â†’ fix permissions â†’ start Jenkins
Docker backup	Host folder via docker cp	Stop container â†’ docker cp back â†’ fix permissions â†’ start container

âœ… Key Notes

Always stop Jenkins before restoring to avoid corruption.

Always fix permissions after copying back (chown -R jenkins:jenkins).

Store backups in remote/cloud storage for disaster recovery.

Test restoration periodically to ensure backups are valid.

